Mission.Author: KingRaptor
Mission.Description: Use your aircraft to assist your ally in defeating the enemy!
Mission.Name: Air Force Command

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message
TriggerLogic.Message:
Scramble! Enemy gunships are inbound to hit our front lines!
Launch available fighters to intercept and destroy all bandits!

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
The Swift is your basic multirole fighter. Fast-flying and extremely fragile, it is well suited to taking out any enemy aircraft that can't fight back. It can also harass enemy ground forces, albeit not very effectively.
A key feature of the Swift is its speed boost ability, invaluable for getting quickly to (or away from) a fight.

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Intecept and destroy the enemy gunships attacking our defenses.
TriggerLogic.Title: Destroy Gunships

TriggerLogic.Message:
Good shooting. That should give us some breathing room.
We're just getting started, though. Intel reports large enemy forces are preparing to hit our defense lines. Be prepared for anything.
Build additional fighters from your Aircraft Plant as needed.

Heads up! Large groups of light units are moving to attack our base.
Defend the Singularity Reactor at all costs! If it blows, we're done for here.
This situation is ideal for the Phoenix napalm bomber. You're cleared to build Phoenixes at your Aircraft Plant.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
-- spawn our Phoenixes slightly offmap and have them fly to us local x = Game.mapSizeX * 0.6 local y = 150 local z = Game.mapSizeZ * 1.2
local tx = Game.mapSizeX * 0.7 local tz = Game.mapSizeZ * 0.8 local ty = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx, tz)
for i=1,4 do local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("corhurc2", x, y, z, "north", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) -- because CreateUnit clamps offmap positions Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.IDLEMODE, {1}, {}) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {tx, ty, tz}, {}) x = x + 48 tx = tx + 48 end

TriggerLogic.Description: The Singularity Reactor in the middle of our base is an extremely valuable asset. Protect it at all costs.
TriggerLogic.Title: Defend Singularity Reactor

TriggerLogic.Message:
The Phoenix drops several napalm bombs that scorch large groups of units, and even sets them on fire for brief periods of time. Like all bombers, it must return to an Air Repair/Rearm Pad after each run in order to rearm.
HINT: Use the Area Attack command (Alt+A) for bombers to attack random targets within the designated circle. Or drag a circle with the standard attack command to hit all targets in the circle in sequence.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
-- spawn Banshees offmap and have them attack our base -- half of the time they'll try a sneaky flank attack, be warned! local mx = Game.mapSizeX local mz = Game.mapSizeZ
local units = {}
local waypointList = { { {mx * 0.2, mz * 0.5}, {mx * 0.2, mz * 0.95} }, { {mx * 0.8, mz * 0.5}, {mx * 0.8, mz * 0.95} }, { {mx * 0.5, mz * 0.5}, {mx * 0.5, mz * 0.95} }, { {mx * 0.5, mz * 0.5}, {mx * 0.5, mz * 0.95} }, }
local waypoints = waypointList[math.random(#waypointList)]
local x = mx* 0.64 - 48 local y = 150 local z = mz * -0.3
local num = 3 if Spring.GetGameSeconds() > 7*60 then num = 4 end
local function SpawnUnits() for i=1,num do local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("armkam", x, y, z, "south", 2) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) -- because CreateUnit clamps offmap positions units[unitID] = true x = x + 48 end end SpawnUnits()
x = mx * 0.36 - 48 SpawnUnits()
for unitID in pairs(units) do Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.IDLEMODE, {0}, {}) local tx, tz = waypoints[1][1], waypoints[1][2] local ty = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx, tz) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {tx, ty, tz}, {"shift"}) tx, tz = waypoints[2][1], waypoints[2][2] ty = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx, tz) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {tx, ty, tz}, {"shift"}) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Recommend putting your factory on Repeat, Commander. It'll save you the trouble of having to constantly select new units to build.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message
TriggerLogic.Message:
Damn! They've started deploying Rapier gunships. These things can take our Swifts in a brawl and come out on top.
We need something harder-hitting. You're cleared to deploy Hawk air superiority fighters. They have the durability to take whatever the Rapiers can throw at them and keep on ticking.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
-- spawn our Hawks slightly offmap and have them move to patrol the pass local x = Game.mapSizeX * 1.4 local y = 150 local z = Game.mapSizeZ * 0.6
local tx1 = Game.mapSizeX * 0.6 local tz = Game.mapSizeZ * 0.5 local ty1 = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx1, tz)
local tx2 = Game.mapSizeX * 0.4 local ty2 = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx1, tz)
for i=1,6 do local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("corvamp", x, y, z, "north", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) -- because CreateUnit clamps offmap positions Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.IDLEMODE, {1}, {}) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {tx1, ty1, tz}, {"shift"}) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.PATROL, {tx2, ty2, tz}, {"shift"}) z = z + 128 end

-- spawn Avengers offmap and have them attack our base local mx = Game.mapSizeX local mz = Game.mapSizeZ
local units = {}
local waypointList = { { {mx * 0.2, mz * 0.5}, {mx * 0.4, mz * 0.95} }, { {mx * 0.8, mz * 0.5}, {mx * 0.6, mz * 0.95} }, { {mx * 0.5, mz * 0.5}, {mx * 0.5, mz * 0.95} }, }
local waypoints = waypointList[math.random(#waypointList)]
local x = mx* 0.64 - 96 local y = 150 local z = mz * -0.3
local time = Spring.GetGameSeconds()
local function SpawnUnits() for i=1,4 do local unitname = "fighter" if i==4 and time > 60*8 then unitname = "corvamp" end local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit(unitname, x, y, z, "south", 2) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) -- because CreateUnit clamps offmap positions units[unitID] = true x = x + 48 end end SpawnUnits()
x = mx * 0.36 - 48 SpawnUnits()
for unitID in pairs(units) do Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.IDLEMODE, {0}, {}) local tx, tz = waypoints[1][1], waypoints[1][2] local ty = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx, tz) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {tx, ty, tz}, {"shift"}) tx, tz = waypoints[2][1], waypoints[2][2] ty = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx, tz) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {tx, ty, tz}, {"shift"}) end

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
The Hawk air superiority fighter is designed for wresting control of the skies from Swifts and Rapiers. Its tough armor lets it survive a considerable amount of anti-air fire.
Hawks have no air-to-ground capability.

These guys don't know when to quit, do they? We've got some heavy firepower bearing down on us: Reaper assault tanks and Pillager mobile artillery pieces.
This looks like a job for the Raven precision bomber. Use it to pick off the Pillagers and any other high-value targets. You can hit the Reapers too, but they're best left to the ground forces.
And watch out! Angler AA bots may be accompanying the enemy.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
-- spawn our Ravens slightly offmap and have them fly to us local x = Game.mapSizeX * 1.3 local y = 150 local z = Game.mapSizeZ
local tx = Game.mapSizeX * 0.7 local tz = Game.mapSizeZ * 0.8 local ty = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx, tz)
for i=1,5 do local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("corshad", x, y, z, "west", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) -- because CreateUnit clamps offmap positions Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.IDLEMODE, {1}, {}) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {tx, ty, tz}, {}) x = x + 128 tx = tx + 128 end

TriggerLogic.Message: The Raven drops a high damage bomb that inflicts heavy damage to a single target. Somewhat slower and sturdier than the Phoenix, it excels at picking off high value targets such as Fusion Reactors and heavy artillery, and can also take down assault units with enough hits.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
-- spawn some Banshees for our ally to help him hold the pass local x = Game.mapSizeX * 0.45 local y = 150 local z = Game.mapSizeZ * 1.3
local tx = Game.mapSizeX * 0.45 local tz = Game.mapSizeZ * 0.5 local ty = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx, tz)
local function SpawnUnits() for i=1,2 do local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("armkam", x, y, z, "north", 4) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) -- because CreateUnit clamps offmap positions Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.IDLEMODE, {0}, {}) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {tx, ty, tz}, {}) x = x + 48 tx = tx + 48 end end
SpawnUnits()
x = Game.mapSizeX * 0.55 tx = Game.mapSizeX * 0.55 ty = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx, tz)
SpawnUnits()

TriggerLogic.Message:
Unbelievable! They're really pulling out all the stops this time - that's a Bantha heavy strider!
We might stand a chance if we can stun the bad guys long enough to keep them from overrunning us while the Ravens work on the Bantha. Use the Thunderbird disarming bomber to stun the Bantha and its little friends!

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
-- spawn our Thunderbirds slightly offmap and have them fly to us local x = Game.mapSizeX * 0.6 local y = 150 local z = Game.mapSizeZ * 1.2
local tx = Game.mapSizeX * 0.7 local tz = Game.mapSizeZ * 0.8 local ty = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx, tz)
for i=1,3 do local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("armstiletto_laser", x, y, z, "north", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) -- because CreateUnit clamps offmap positions Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.IDLEMODE, {1}, {}) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {tx, ty, tz}, {}) x = x + 48 tx = tx + 48 end

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Take out the Bantha heavy strider attacking our base. This should bring the enemy's offensive to a halt.
TriggerLogic.Title: Destroy the Bantha

TriggerLogic.Message:
The Thunderbird "bomber" doesn't drop bombs at all. Instead, it fires a storm of lightning bolts as it overflies the target area, disabling the weapons, construction and combat abilities of any units caught in it for up to fifteen seconds. It is particularly effective against area shields or large groups of shieldbots.
Hard targets will generally require multiple passes in close sequence in order to be completely disabled.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
-- add a pair of Brawlers to the emergency reinforcements local x = Game.mapSizeX * 0.45 local y = 150 local z = Game.mapSizeZ * 1.3
local tx = Game.mapSizeX * 0.45 local tz = Game.mapSizeZ * 0.5 local ty = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx, tz)
local function SpawnUnits() local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("armbrawl", x, y, z, "north", 4) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) -- because CreateUnit clamps offmap positions Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.IDLEMODE, {0}, {}) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {tx, ty, tz}, {}) end
SpawnUnits()
x = Game.mapSizeX * 0.55 tx = Game.mapSizeX * 0.55 ty = Spring.GetGroundHeight(tx, tz)
SpawnUnits()

Spring.KillTeam(3) local units = Spring.GetAllUnits()
for i=1,#units do local unitID = units[i] local allyTeam = Spring.GetUnitAllyTeam(unitID) if allyTeam == 1 then Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {Game.mapSizeX*0.5, 0, 0}, {} ) end end

TriggerLogic.Message:
Huzzah! The enemy's ace in the hole has been destroyed and they are now in full retreat!
Do not pursue. Your work here is done, Commander - return to base.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local frame = Spring.GetGameFrame() local PAR_TIME = 30*60*18 -- 18 minutes local bonus = (PAR_TIME - frame) * 5
local score = (GG.mission.scores[0]) + bonus GG.mission.scores[0] = score Spring.SetTeamRulesParam(0, "score", score)
